                             parent="aspace_b3d5972eb53be81677c40af095a60d36">2</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_6bbcda8395547d2fcd2e9f46e1ec7aed">
                  <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
                  <p>Asking Gonzaga to help him acquire a violin that had been bought for him in Cremona, emphasizing the high quality of the instrument and its good condition; he also reports composing sonatas for solo violin for the Prince</p>
               </scopecontent>
               <bioghist id="aspace_6a80c1d11bd8d3d4f769314b876eac88">
                  <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
                  <p>Buonamente dedicated several works to Monteverdi and probably played under his direction</p>
               </bioghist>
            </c>
            <c id="ref23" level="file">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Capece, Alessandro (d.after 1635). Music, holograph</unittitle>
                  <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">circa 1617-1624</unitdate>
                  <physdesc id="aspace_adab96168434f3bff5ba4bc911a9e7a3">Bound in contemporary vellum boards; painted arms on cover [Sulmona (Abruzzi)]; </physdesc>
                  <physdesc id="aspace_f8f2d629eac95a854d2fda35995586ec">24 pages, 4to</physdesc>
