                             parent="aspace_e40261bd5b29b5b6f0a7ce71be2755c2">3</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_bb3c4c2229c355c7ced716aa99cbf828">
                  <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
                  <p>Contains three dialogues for two voices and continuo: <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
                        <part>La fede e la speranza</part>
                     </title>, for bass and alto; <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
                        <part>Venere et Arione</part>
                     </title>, for soprano and tenor, and <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
                        <part>Armida e Rinaldo</part>
                     </title>, for soprano and tenor; and a madrigal, <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
                        <part>Morte soccorsa</part>
                     </title>, for solo voice and continuo</p>
                  <p>Dedication, signed, to Marc-Antonio Borghese, Prince of Sulmona</p>
               </scopecontent>
               <bioghist id="aspace_22001883428acfeff9a094e25088154c">
                  <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
                  <p>Capece was maestro di cappella at Ferrara, Rieti (1616), Sulmona (1617-1624) and Tivoli (1624-1627)</p>
               </bioghist>
            </c>
